---

# How It Works

## CIDR Parsing

CIDR ranges are parsed manually using bitmask operations:

```text id="9up7v7"
network = ip & subnet_mask
broadcast = network | !subnet_mask
```

Hosts are generated by iterating between the network and broadcast addresses.

Single IPs are also supported automatically.

---

## Concurrent Scanning

Each host is scanned concurrently using Tokio tasks:

```rust id="g8b0vr"
task::spawn(async move {
    scan_ports(ip_addr, ports).await
});
```

Each port scan is also executed concurrently.

---

## Service Probes

Protocols are implemented using a trait abstraction:

```rust id="2ly2g0"
#[async_trait]
pub trait ServiceProbe {
    async fn probe(
        &self,
        stream: &mut TcpStream,
    ) -> std::io::Result<Option<String>>;
}
```

This allows protocol-specific probing logic to be added easily.

